# Architecture Reference

## Model (~2M params, BTR core)
- Transformer: 3 encoder layers, 4 heads, hidden_dim=256, FFN=512, pre-norm + GELU
- CLS token pooling -> concat with account MLP -> LayerNorm -> elementwise gate by IQN cosine-tau embedding -> NoisyLinear dueling heads
- Distributional head: **IQN** (Dabney et al. 2018) replacing the old C51 fixed-support categorical. Online K=64, target K'=64, policy K=32. Quantile-Huber loss with kappa=1.0.
- TD target: **Munchausen DQN** (Vieillard et al. 2020) layered onto the IQN bootstrap — ``alpha=0.9``, entropy temperature ``tau_M=0.03``, log-pi clip floor ``-1.0``. Target network is the only network consulted by the target path; online net is reserved for the loss-side ``Z(s_t, a_t, tau)`` only.
- **Spectral normalization** wraps ``weight_mu`` of every NoisyLinear inside ``value_stream`` and ``advantage_stream`` (toggle: ``spectral_norm_enabled``). Encoder, ``aux_return_head``, and ``tau_embedding`` are *not* normalized.
- Auxiliary return-prediction head on CLS output (0.1 weight MSE loss on log_return_1 feature)
- Polyak soft target updates (tau=0.001, every learner step)

## Features (12 channels)
- Columns 0-5 (raw): open, high, low, close, volume, transactions -> window-level z-score at observation time
- Columns 6-11 (derived, precomputed in .npz): log_return_1, log_return_5, log_return_10, realized_vol, volume_ratio, hl_range_ratio -> clipped to [-10, 10]
- ACCOUNT_STATE_DIM = 5: position_frac, cash_frac, unrealized_pnl, bars_in_position/60, cumulative_fees/initial_balance

## Data Pipeline
- Raw CSV -> extract_raw.py -> split_data.py -> preprocess_npz.py --clean -> .npz files (required before training)
- Each .npz: close_prices (float32) + features (float32, [T, 12])
- DataManager prefers .npz, falls back to CSV
- Current data: train 2017-01 to 2024-09, val 2024-10, test 2024-11 to 2025-04 (stale as of Apr 2026 -- refresh from Massive/Polygon after baseline training run)
- Source: Massive (formerly Polygon) minute-bar aggregates for USD crypto pairs

## Training
- bfloat16 autocast (no GradScaler), torch.compile required
- IQN has unbounded support (no v_min/v_max ceiling); reward_scale=1.0 keeps per-step rewards O(1e-4 to 1e-3) and n-step returns well within numerical range. The Munchausen log-pi bonus is bounded by ``alpha * tau_M * log_pi_clip = 0.9 * 0.03 * -1 = -0.027`` per step.
- No action masking needed (target allocation actions are always valid)
- Curriculum learning: training file pool ramps from 30% to 100% over episodes
- Progress tracked in models/progress.jsonl (one JSONL line per episode/validation)
- Replay buffer checkpointed on save/resume

## Environment
- 6 target-allocation actions: 0%, 20%, 40%, 60%, 80%, 100% exposure
- Agent picks desired position size; environment computes the buy/sell delta
- Every action is always valid (no action masking needed)
- Benchmark-relative reward: reward_scale * ((market_return + trade_return) - benchmark_frac * price_return) - lambda * incremental_drawdown
- min_trade_notional: $10 minimum (matches Alpaca live requirement)
- Slippage: configurable basis points on all trades
- Termination: portfolio < 1% of initial balance

## Key Constraints
- torch.compile wraps networks in OptimizedModule; always use `is not None` checks, never truthiness
- Old checkpoints incompatible after architecture changes (different dims). Pre-IQN (C51) checkpoints are rejected at load time by ``agent_checkpoint._assert_iqn_state_dict``; use ``scripts/migrate_c51_to_iqn.py`` once to warm-start from the encoder + aux head of an old ``best_*.pt``.
- Live trader (momentum_live) must match training normalization exactly (window-level z-score + derived features)
- Live inference loads checkpoints with `inference_only=True` (eager forward, no compile); default device is CPU. Set `MOMENTUM_LIVE_DEVICE=cuda` for GPU inference. Training still requires CUDA + compile (`inference_only=False`).
- Live runs one `MomentumLiveTrader` per symbol against an isolated Alpaca Broker sub-account (one sub-account per pair, JNLC-funded from a designated firm account). The agent stays single-asset; per-pair cash isolation matches the training distribution and removes the multi-asset cash-pool race condition.
